cs.RO, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a robotic arm that can recognize human voice commands and is tested in different environments to perform tasks.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper deals with speech recognition and noise perturbations.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a more intuitive approach to control robots using natural language processing.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper focuses on enhancing the ability of robots to interact with humans using their natural form of communication.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with speech recognition and natural language processing.
